{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"7c1daf8f-8709-43e0-a451-0c1bbc62166b","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Designed the typed-evidence-gate change and wrote design.md, spec.md, and tasks.md under specrunner/changes/typed-evidence-gate/ on branch change/typed-evidence-gate-18cecd72.\n\nPlan summary:\n- Add `Evidence = { checked; skipped; unverified }` to kernel/report-result.ts; extend `JudgeReportResult` with optional `evidence`.\n- Enforce evidence at parse time in `parseJudgeReportInput` (new `parseEvidence` helper), which the shared JUDGE_REPORT_TOOL singleton and the delegating code-review/conformance parsers inherit; request-review and producer contracts untouched.\n- Add `evidence` to the three judge tool zodSchemas + descriptions.\n- Extend `deriveJudgeVerdict(findings, ok, evidence?)`: `checked === 0` → escalation (vacuous); `checked > 0` and `undefined`-evidence paths preserve existing derivation. `deriveConformanceVerdict` forwards evidence. `deriveRegressionGateVerdict` and `deriveRequestReviewVerdict` unchanged.\n- Widen `judgeVerdictFn` type; wire evidence through step-completion with a stderr diagnostic surfacing \"検証実績ゼロ\"; widen persisted `StepOutcome.toolResult` / `StepResultInput.toolResult` optionally (backward-compat: past records not re-evaluated).\n- New single-source `EVIDENCE_COUNTS_DEFINITION` fragment injected into the 5 judge prompts (not request-review).\n- Tests: vacuous derivation, parse enforcement, legacy-record read/resume, prompt drift-guard, plus flagged follow-on fixture updates (pipeline-mock-client and judge-tool integration tests must add evidence to stay approved).\n\nKey scoping decisions documented: because JUDGE_REPORT_TOOL is a load-bearing singleton, regression-gate also reports evidence, but its verdict fn is deliberately left unchanged (vacuous non-applicable; skipWhen makes checked=0 unreachable) — keeping the change within the request's \"judge 系のみ / deriveJudgeVerdict\" scope without splitting the singleton. No source files outside the change folder were edited.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-21T06:51:59.108Z","endedAt":"2026-07-21T07:06:42.819Z","commitOid":"bdc8dd2b3d33fb2fe739a698712b682ff3a20f65"}
